prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "crimson-ink-manga-dossier" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules:
- Composition: make one original hand-drawn manga hero fill roughly two thirds of the frame in a dramatic low-angle or close wide-angle view. Place an enormous cropped headline behind the hero. Surround the figure with six to ten asymmetric newspaper dossier modules, monochrome manga insets, quote blocks, diagrams, and a lower information card. Let the figure break across the editorial grid.
- Typography: use extra-bold condensed uppercase sans-serif for the huge distressed headline, compact condensed section labels, small serif newsprint columns, and one large crimson pull quote. Keep the supplied main text readable and use only original copy.
- Color: restrict the page to warm off-white paper, carbon black, grayscale screentone, and deep crimson red. Use crimson only for the headline, selected character zones, diagrams, architectural silhouettes, rules, and controlled ink accents.
- Texture and lighting: render crisp variable-weight manga ink linework, hatching, hard cel-like value separation, coarse halftone, aged uncoated paper grain, dry-brush wear, slight offset misregistration, and sharp white highlights.
- Graphic elements: use rule lines, boxed dossiers, cropped manga frames, interview Q-and-A blocks, warning labels, radial or technical diagrams, city or industrial silhouettes, caption strips, torn wedges, and restrained ink splatter. Adapt these modules laterally for landscape and vertically for portrait.

Avoid: any recognizable copyrighted character, franchise name, official manga panel, copied pose, copied wording, exact source layout, logo, publisher mark, watermark, username, QR code, platform UI, celebrity likeness, glossy full-color anime screenshot, photoreal portrait, 3D render, soft pastel illustration, clean corporate brochure, excessive digital noise, blur, malformed hands, unreadable giant headline, or chaotic text clutter.

Important content rule: match the high-density crimson manga dossier visual family first, then change the source content completely. Use the specified original subject, action, prop, setting, text, costume, diagrams, and story premise while preserving every style fidelity anchor.
